ng.\n\n177\n\nQM in Practice (part I)\n\n[34] Overview of prototype model systems\n\nBelow we consider some simple one-particle closed systems in 0D/1D/2D/3D.", "embedding": [-0.0072225877, -0.0054206434, 0.062235396, -0.008020007, -0.040334098, -0.008027871, -0.013530974, -0.009334914, -0.05281138, 0.06809464, 0.04981615, 0.007136712, 0.016586201, -0.00049534906, -0.04483559, 0.048828296, -0.004792842, -0.0036850176, -0.0991138, 0.02760053, 0.008981502, -0.020167455, -0.07489342, -0.019173503, -0.012269064, 0.04269525, 0.033779185, 0.03176981, 0.07840042, 0.019840484, 0.034266606, -0.036222063, 0.0064831786, -0.042542446, -0.006709523, -0.028510183, 0.011458351, -0.034325168, 0.019978272, -0.024783941, 0.07008434, 0.0067974217, 0.021984972, -0.007895668, -0.0169665, -0.009115329, 0.001336241, -0.01855014, -0.02309928, -0.04092208, 0.0041719205, -0.008400099, 0.004905699, -0.05559322, -0.010752618, -0.0015057132, 0.012808583, 0.021241475, -0.022846214, 0.003408523, 0.047311954, 0.011273169, 0.015871082, -0.016699249, -0.016262835, 0.07153057, -0.008965982, 0.05834349, -0.025911113, -0.015468755, -0.0077971546, -0.023454517, 0.014066752, -0.018430203, -0.041643854, 0.015578344, 0.0035842694, -0.015614116, -0.04109471, 0.031623684, 0.005050237, 0.0027956013, 0.023771962, 0.007770035, -0.0039048665, -0.019192928, -0.011031462, 0.003846902, 0.023405626, 0.020806246, 0.048486065, 0.06865701, -0.027498292, -0.012108703, -2.506181e-05, 0.02350669, -0.0054284735, 0.011470022, 0.03247752, 0.016632712, 0.004859367, 0.00912498, -0.008639758, 0.012641808, -0.062102865, 0.04685909, -0.019085227, 0.04706539, 0.020765074, -0.017440198, 0.016793353, 0.0044064755, 0.0069606244, 0.029767739, -0.0046515283, 0.02909095, 0.026684107, 0.03248882, -0.021689009, -0.009886012, 0.0027651528, 0.029618122, 0.035590496, -0.004312761, 0.030803293, -8.3497885e-05, 0.006280641, -0.00155924, -0.036218595, -0.028985843, -0.002911067, -0.019402148, 0.039180387, 0.033064224, -0.009808749, 0.0078116828